briefdescription.para: Returns the deterministic hazard rate component.

detaileddescription.para: survival probability calculation implemented in terms of the hazard rate $ h(t) $ as \[S(t) = \exp\left( - \int_0^t h(\tau) d\tau \right). \]

simplesect.para: This default implementation uses numerical integration, which might be inefficient and inaccurate. Derived classes should override it if a more efficient implementation is available.

detaileddescription.para: Probability of default conditional to the realization of a given value of the stochastic part of the hazard rate at a prior time (and thus to survival at that time). $ P_{surv}(\tau>tTarget|F_{tFwd}) $
